<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[761,1353,2230,2653]" lastBlockId="22.[149,1354,2660,3088]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[763,1042,2466,2495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 116-130 mm, tail 12-16 mm, hindfoot 13:-5-15-5 mm; weight 33-51-8 g. Tail is-4:5—13-3% of head-body length. Dental formulais13/2,C1/1,P4/4,M 3/3 (x2) = 42. Chromosomal complement from Vietnam has 2n = 30 and FNa = 52.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[149,1354,2660,3088]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[150,261,2699,2732]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Habitat.</emphasis>
Farmland and possibly forests. In Vietnam, La Touche’s Mole occupies lower elevations when sympatric with Kuznetsov’s Mole (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1940" box="[887,1041,2739,2772]" class="Mammalia" family="Talpidae" genus="Euroscaptor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="617" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Euroscaptor</taxonomicName>
kuznetsovi) or Orlov’s Mole (E. orlovi).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
